example.p:
Consider the Boolean expression \(f\left(x_1, x_2\right) =x_1 \lor \overline{x_2} \). One method of
determining the minterm normal form of f is to think in terms of sets. Consider the diagram with the usual translation of notation in . Then 

\begin{split}
f\left(x_1, x_2\right)&=\left(\overline{x_1}\land \overline{x_2}\right)\lor \left(x_1\land \overline{x_2}\right)\lor \left(x_1\land
x_2\right)\\
	& = M_{00} \lor M_{10} \lor M_{11}
\end{split}
